		<p>&gt; Good methods make use of more information.</p>
<p>How should one practice regression discontinuity designs and other local average treatment effect-estimating designs in light of this ethos?</p>

		<div class="reply"><a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='http://andrewgelman.com/2016/09/12/bayesian-statistics-then-and-now/?replytocom=306642#respond' onclick='return addComment.moveForm( "div-comment-306642", "306642", "respond", "29914" )' aria-label='Reply to Lauren'>Reply to this comment</a></div>
