		<li class="comment byuser comment-author-bob_carpenter even depth-2 parent" id="comment-308111">
				<div id="div-comment-308111" class="comment-body">
				<div class="comment-author vcard">
			<img alt='' src='http://1.gravatar.com/avatar/77f083909d955b715846250a33340a14?s=32&#038;d=mm&#038;r=g' srcset='http://1.gravatar.com/avatar/77f083909d955b715846250a33340a14?s=64&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g 2x' class='avatar avatar-32 photo' height='32' width='32' />			<cite class="fn"><a href='http://lingpipe-blog.com/' rel='external nofollow' class='url'>Bob Carpenter</a></cite> <span class="says">says:</span>		</div>
		
		<div class="comment-meta commentmetadata"><a href="http://andrewgelman.com/2016/09/12/bayesian-statistics-then-and-now/#comment-308111">
			September 13, 2016 at 10:22 am</a>		</div>

		<p>I used the Efron and Morris data for my <a href="http://mc-stan.org/documentation/case-studies/pool-binary-trials.html" rel="nofollow">Stan case study on Bayesian hierarchical modeling for repeated binary trials</a>.  But I pointed out it&#8217;s the exact same model as used in the BUGS surgical example (mortality in pediatric surgeries) and the <i>Bayesian Data Analysis</i> book&#8217;s first hierarchical example on rat tumors in a clinical study.  I think the baseball example is nice because it&#8217;s a not identical but fairly homogeneous population where pooling helps a lot and everyone who knows baseball can understand it.  That only leaves us needing an example that the rest of the world can easily understand.  The problem with more involved examples is that the simplicitly of the analysis and the pedagogical point can get lost in the messy data analysis details.  As a computer scientist, I was trained to create the simplest possible working example of every concept in introductory material.</p>

		<div class="reply"><a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='http://andrewgelman.com/2016/09/12/bayesian-statistics-then-and-now/?replytocom=308111#respond' onclick='return addComment.moveForm( "div-comment-308111", "308111", "respond", "29914" )' aria-label='Reply to Bob Carpenter'>Reply to this comment</a></div>
